 <fr:p>We will use the same method as in our proof of <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MI"
href="jms-00MI.xml"
taxon="Lemma" />.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> be a non-empty subset of an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link> set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, so that we have some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex>. We define <fr:tex
